XML_CASESUMMARY.SUMMARY:
This three-vehicle crash occurred in a rural area on a four-lane divided roadway with an extended median. The southbound lanes curve right and are on a downhill elevation. There are paved shoulders on the left and right side of the southbound lanes. The speed limit for the area is 88 kmph (55 mph) and there is a posted advisory speed limit of 72 kmph (45 mph) for the curve. Also present are Chevron warning signs for the long, continuous curve. The crash occurred during daylight with no adverse weather or road conditions present.
Vehicle one (V1), a 1998 Dodge Ram pickup was southbound in the first lane when it steered right to avoid vehicle two (V2) which was rapidly decelerating in front in the same lane. The rear left side plane of vehicle one contacted the rear end plane of V2, a 2004 Jeep Cherokee. V2 was slowing very quickly to avoid a pedestrian who was crossing the travel lanes from the right to the left. The pedestrian was the driver of vehicle three (V3), a 2002 Honda Odyssey mini-van that was parked on the right side paved shoulder of the southbound lanes. After the impact with V2, V1 departed the first lane and with its front-end plane contacted the rear end plane of V3. V1 then departed the road edge and struck the embankment edge with its front-end plane and came to rest. V2 continued forward and was impacted on its right side plane by the front left corner of V3 which had rotated counter-clockwise after the impact with V1. V2 came to a controlled stop on the right shoulder. V3 came to rest on the right shoulder. V1 and V3 were towed due to damage. V2 was driven from the scene.
The driver of V1, a forty-five year old male was not interviewed. There is no known pre-crash information for this driver.
The driver of V2, a nineteen-year-old male was not interviewed. There is no known pre-crash information for this driver.
The critical pre-crash event for V1 was coded: other vehicle in lane, traveling in same direction while decelerating. The critical reason for the critical pre-crash event for V1 was coded: Type of driver error unknown.
The critical pre-crash event for V2 was coded: pedestrian, pedal cyclist; pedestrian in roadway. The critical reason for the critical pre-crash event was not coded to this vehicle.
